The paper discusses the development of provably accurate and efficient algorithms for low-rank matrix factorization via nonconvex optimization. This topic is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), information theory (cs.IT), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and signal processing (cs.SI). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG and cs.CV, followed by cs.IT, cs.NA, and cs.SI.
